text: The 1994 Navy Midshipmen football team represented the United States Naval Academy (USNA) during the 1994 NCAA Division I-A football season. Navy competed as an independent with no conference affiliation. The team was led by fifth-year head coach George Chaump.The team had plenty of talent on both sides of the ball. On offense,they had star QB Jim Kubiak and NFL-bound tight end Kevin Hickman. On defense,they had loads of talent,such as DB Robert Green and Monster D-lineman Tom Neville. ==Schedule== ==Personnel== ==References== Navy Midshipmen Category:Navy Midshipmen football seasons Nav
